[44.594767, "o", "\r\n"]
[44.601798, "o", "\r\n  \u001b[1menvpod security audit\u001b[0m \u001b[2m· browser-wayland\u001b[0m\r\n\r\n  \u001b[2mPod boundary\u001b[0m  \u001b[32m17\u001b[0m/17 with default user\r\n\r\n  \u001b[33m⚠\u001b[0m 6 security notes:\r\n\r\n  \u001b[1mN-03\u001b[0m  \u001b[31m[HIGH]\u001b[0m Direct DNS bypass possible\r\n"]
[44.601979, "o", "        \u001b[2mdns.mode is Blacklist — direct IP queries bypass domain filtering.\u001b[0m\r\n        Fix: use dns.mode: Whitelist to block all non-allowed traffic.\r\n\r\n  \u001b[1mS-03\u001b[0m  \u001b[31m[HIGH]\u001b[0m Relaxed seccomp profile\r\n        \u001b[2mseccomp_profile is browser — allows clone3, unshare, and other syscalls blocked by default.\u001b[0m\r\n        Fix: remove security.seccomp_profile or set to default if browser features are not needed.\r\n\r\n  \u001b[1mP-03\u001b[0m  \u001b[33m[MEDIUM]\u001b[0m Nested namespaces possible\r\n        \u001b[2mseccomp_profile is browser — unshare/clone3 allow nested namespace creation.\u001b[0m\r\n        Fix: remove security.seccomp_profile or set to default if browser features are not needed.\r\n\r\n  \u001b[1mI-04\u001b[0m  \u001b[2m[LOW]\u001b[0m Wayland display access — client isolation enforced by compositor\r\n        \u001b[2mdevices.display is true with Wayland — compositor prevents cross-client keylogging and screenshot.\u001b[0m\r\n        Fix: set devices.display: false if GUI access is not needed.\r\n\r\n  \u001b[1mI-05\u001b[0m  \u001b[33m[MEDIUM]\u001b[0m Audio access available (PipeWire — finer-grained permissions)\r\n        \u001b[2mdevices.audio is true with PipeWire — audio access with finer-grained permission model.\u001b[0m\r\n        Fix: set devices.audio: false if audio is not needed.\r\n\r\n  \u001b[1mI-06\u001b[0m  \u001b[2m[LOW]\u001b[0m GPU information leakage\r\n        \u001b[2mdevices.gpu is true — nvidia-smi exposes host GPU model to the agent.\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[44.602031, "o", "        Fix: set devices.gpu: false if GPU access is not needed.\r\n\r\n  \u001b[32m✓\u001b[0m 6 checks passed (user, memory, cpu, pids, display (wayland), ...)\r\n\r\n"]
[46.605376, "o", "\r\n\u001b[2m# Wayland + PipeWire: display is LOW risk, audio is MEDIUM.\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[49.608473, "o", "\r\n\r\n"]
[49.608566, "o", "\u001b[2m# Compare that to X11 — CRITICAL, because X11 allows keylogging across windows.\u001b[0m\r\n"]
[52.611508, "o", "\r\n"]
[52.611825, "o", "\u001b[0;32m$ \u001b[0m"]
[52.611929, "o", "s"]
[52.654434, "o", "u"]
[52.697013, "o", "d"]
[52.739549, "o", "o"]
[52.782214, "o", " "]
